de.esoco.lib.expression.predicate

Class PredicateJoin<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.obrel.core.RelatedObject
      • de.esoco.lib.expression.function.AbstractFunction<T,java.lang.Boolean>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.function.Function<T,java.lang.Boolean>, java.util.function.Predicate<T>, Relatable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Predicates.And, Predicates.Or

    public abstract class PredicateJoin<T>
extends AbstractPredicate<T>
    Base class for joins of two predicates (like logical combinations). Subclasses must implement the Function.evaluate(Object) method to implement the actual join of the two predicates in the correct order. The predicates can be queried with the methods getLeft() and getRight().

      • paramsEqual

        protected boolean paramsEqual(AbstractFunction<?,?> rOther)
        Description copied from class: AbstractFunction
        This method must be overridden by subclasses that define additional function parameters to compare these parameters for equality with another function instance. It will be invoked by this classes' implementation of AbstractFunction.equals(Object) after the standard equality checks have been performed. A subclass can safely assume that the other function argument is not NULL and of exactly the same class as itself. The default implementation always returns TRUE.
